chmod = change file mode
change user or group (r)read, (w)write or (x)execute permissions on files and folders

ls -l shows you
-uuugggooo ... <file name>
duuugggooo ... <folder name>

u = user
g = groups
o = other (everybody)

give permissions
sudo chmod u+r <file name>
sudo chmod u+w <file name>
sudo chmod u+x <file name>


take away permissions
sudo chmod u-x <file name>
sudo chmod u-rwx <file name>


apply to all files in folder
sudo chmod --recursive

you can change permissions numerically
sudo chmod 700 <file name> - all permissions for user
sudo chmod 644 <file name> - default file permissions
sudo chmod 777 <file name> - all permissions for all

numeric system is
r = 4
w = 2
x = 1



